-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/barclays-s-meli-to-head-credit-research-rogoff-to-helm-strategy.html
Barclays Capital (BARC) , the securities
unit of Barclays Plc, has appointed Jeffrey Meli to head of
credit research from his role leading the credit strategy team.  Meli will report to Barclays Capital research head Larry Kantor instead of former supervisor Jon Scoffin, who directs
research in the Asia-Pacific region and who will be adding
responsibility for equities there, according to an internal memo
obtained by Bloomberg News.  Bradley Rogoff will succeed Meli in heading global credit
strategy research from his role leading U.S. credit strategy
research, according to the memo. Thomas Walsh, head of global
high-grade credit research at Barclays Capital, will fill a new
position as head of fundamental credit research, according to
the memo.  Seth Martin, a  Barclays Capital  spokesman, confirmed the
contents of the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
